<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Curriculum Builder — CSHealthED</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
*,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
body{font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;background:#f0f4fb;color:#1a2340;min-height:100vh}
nav{background:#0d2d6e;height:64px;padding:0 28px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;border-bottom:3px solid #c0392b;position:sticky;top:0;z-index:50}
.nb{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;text-decoration:none}
.nl{width:42px;height:42px;border-radius:50%;background:white;padding:2px;object-fit:contain}
.nn{font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:white}
.nn .t{color:#2ec4b6}.nn .r{color:#c0392b}
.bk{color:#8aaee0;font-size:13px;font-weight:500;text-decoration:none;padding:7px 14px;border-radius:6px;border:1px solid rgba(138,174,224,.3);transition:all .15s}
.bk:hover{background:rgba(255,255,255,.1);color:white}
.page{max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;padding:28px 20px 60px}
.stepbar{display:flex;background:white;border:1px solid #dde3ef;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;margin-bottom:22px}
.sp{flex:1;padding:10px 6px;text-align:center;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:#9aaac5;border-right:1px solid #dde3ef;transition:all .15s}
.sp:last-child{border-right:none}
.sp.active{background:#0d2d6e;color:white}
.sp.done{background:#e6f4ee;color:#167a6b}
.card{background:white;border:1px solid #dde3ef;border-radius:12px;padding:22px;margin-bottom:14px}
.ct{font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#0d2d6e;margin-bottom:16px;padding-bottom:11px;border-bottom:1px solid #eef2f8}
.field{margin-bottom:14px}.field:last-child{margin-bottom:0}
.field>label{display:block;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:#6b7a99;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.7px;margin-bottom:5px}
.field select,.field textarea{width:100%;padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #c8d1e8;border-radius:8px;font-size:14px;color:#1a2340;background:#f8faff;font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;transition:border-color .15s}
.field select:focus,.field textarea:focus{outline:none;border-color:#0d2d6e;box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(13,45,110,.09);background:white}
.field textarea{resize:vertical;min-height:96px;line-height:1.55}
.hint{font-size:11px;color:#9aaac5;margin-top:4px;line-height:1.5}
.two{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:14px}
.rrow{display:flex;gap:7px;flex-wrap:wrap}
.rpill{flex:1;min-width:74px;padding:9px 10px;border:1px solid #c8d1e8;border-radius:7px;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:#6b7a99;background:#f8faff;cursor:pointer;text-align:center;transition:all .15s}
.rpill:hover{border-color:#0d2d6e;color:#0d2d6e}
.rpill.sel{background:#0d2d6e;border-color:#0d2d6e;color:white}
.cklist{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px}
.ckrow{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;padding:9px 12px;border:1px solid #c8d1e8;border-radius:7px;background:#f8faff;cursor:pointer;font-size:13px;color:#1a2340;transition:all .15s;user-select:none}
.ckrow:hover{border-color:#0d2d6e}
.ckrow.sel{border-color:#0d2d6e;background:#eef2ff;color:#0d2d6e;font-weight:600}
.ckrow input{width:15px;height:15px;accent-color:#0d2d6e;flex-shrink:0;pointer-events:none}
.btnrow{display:flex;gap:9px;justify-content:flex-end}
.btn{padding:10px 22px;border-radius:8px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:1px solid #c8d1e8;background:white;color:#1a2340;font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;transition:all .15s}
.btn:hover{background:#f0f4fb}
.btn.pri{background:#0d2d6e;border-color:#0d2d6e;color:white}
.btn.pri:hover{background:#0b2560}
.btn.suc{background:#1a8c4e;border-color:#1a8c4e;color:white}
.btn.suc:hover{background:#157a42}
.lcard{text-align:center;padding:56px 20px}
.spin{width:44px;height:44px;border:4px solid #dde3ef;border-top-color:#0d2d6e;border-radius:50%;animation:spin .75s linear infinite;margin:0 auto 14px}
@keyframes spin{to{transform:rotate(360deg)}}
.lcard h3{font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:#1a2340;margin-bottom:5px}
.lcard p{font-size:12px;color:#9aaac5}
.mgrid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:9px;margin-bottom:16px}
.mt{background:white;border:1px solid #dde3ef;border-radius:9px;padding:11px 8px;text-align:center;border-top:3px solid #0d2d6e}
.mt.r{border-top-color:#c0392b}.mt.o{border-top-color:#d68910}.mt.g{border-top-color:#1a8c4e}
.mt .v{font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:#0d2d6e}.mt.r .v{color:#c0392b}.mt.o .v{color:#d68910}.mt.g .v{color:#1a8c4e}
.mt .l{font-size:9px;font-weight:600;color:#9aaac5;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:2px;letter-spacing:.5px}
.tabbar{display:flex;gap:3px;background:#eef2f8;padding:3px;border-radius:9px;margin-bottom:12px}
.tabbtn{flex:1;padding:8px 5px;border-radius:6px;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;border:none;background:transparent;color:#6b7a99;font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;transition:all .15s}
.tabbtn.on{background:white;color:#0d2d6e;border:1px solid #dde3ef}
.outbody{background:white;border:1px solid #dde3ef;border-radius:10px;padding:20px;font-size:13px;line-height:1.72;color:#1a2340;min-height:280px}
.outbody h2{font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#0d2d6e;margin:16px 0 6px;padding-bottom:4px;border-bottom:1px solid #eef2f8}
.outbody h2:first-child{margin-top:0}
.outbody h3{font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#c0392b;margin:11px 0 4px}
.outbody ul,.outbody ol{padding-left:18px}
.outbody li{margin:2px 0}
.outbody .snote{background:#fffbe6;border-left:3px solid #d68910;border-radius:0 5px 5px 0;padding:7px 11px;margin:7px 0;font-size:12px;font-style:italic}
.outbody hr{border:none;border-top:1px solid #eef2f8;margin:12px 0}
.outbody p{margin:5px 0}
.outbody strong{font-weight:700}
.errbanner{background:#fff0f0;border:1px solid #f5c6cb;border-radius:9px;padding:14px 18px;color:#c0392b;font-size:13px;margin-bottom:14px}
@media(max-width:580px){.two{grid-template-columns:1fr}.mgrid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}.rrow{flex-direction:column}}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <a href="/" class="nb">
    <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="CSHealthED" class="nl">
    <span class="nn"><span style="color:white">CS</span><span class="t">Health</span><span class="r">ED</span></span>
  </a>
  <a href="/" class="bk">← Back to home</a>
</nav>

<div class="page">
  <div id="app"></div>
</div>

<script>
const TOPICS={
  'Preparatory':['EMS systems and medical/legal issues','Workforce safety and wellness','Documentation and EMS communication','Anatomy and physiology','Pathophysiology','Life span development','Principles of pharmacology','Medication administration'],
  'Airway management':['Airway management and ventilation','Oxygenation and oxygen delivery','Artificial ventilation techniques'],
  'Patient assessment':['Scene size-up','Primary assessment (ABCDE)','History-taking (SAMPLE and OPQRST)','Secondary assessment and physical exam','Vital signs and monitoring devices','Reassessment'],
  'Medical emergencies':['Cardiac emergencies and CPR/AED','Respiratory emergencies','Neurological emergencies and stroke','Diabetic and endocrine emergencies','Anaphylaxis and allergic reactions','Toxicology and overdose management','Psychiatric and behavioral emergencies','Abdominal and gastrointestinal emergencies','Infectious disease and sepsis'],
  'Shock and resuscitation':['Shock recognition and management','Cardiac arrest and post-resuscitation care','Respiratory failure and arrest'],
  'Trauma':['Trauma overview and kinematics','Hemorrhage control and bleeding','Chest trauma','Abdominal and genitourinary trauma','Head, neck, and spinal trauma','Orthopedic trauma and splinting','Soft tissue trauma and burns','Environmental emergencies','Multi-system trauma','Pediatric trauma'],
  'Special populations':['Obstetric emergencies and childbirth','Neonatal care and resuscitation','Pediatric emergencies','Geriatric emergencies','Patients with special challenges'],
  'EMS operations':['Ambulance operations and driving safety','Incident command and management','Multiple casualty incidents and triage','Hazardous materials awareness','Vehicle extrication','Air medical operations','Disaster and terrorism response']
};

const EMT_KB=`NEMS STANDARDS: PREPARATORY: EMS history; NHTSA; professionalism; QI; patient safety; PPE; stress mgmt; documentation; HIPAA; scope; consent; negligence; A&P; pathophys; pharmacology; med admin. AIRWAY: anatomy; manual maneuvers; suctioning; OPA/NPA; BVM; O2 delivery; CPAP; peds differences. ASSESSMENT: scene size-up; ABCDE; SAMPLE; OPQRST; vitals; 12-lead basics; stroke scales; reassessment. CARDIAC: ACS/STEMI; aspirin; nitro; CPAP; arrest mgmt; CPR quality; AED; dysrhythmias; post-ROSC; ACLS. RESPIRATORY: asthma/COPD; pulm edema; pneumo; needle decomp; PE; resp failure. NEURO: stroke (FAST); seizures; AMS (AEIOU-TIPS); herniation. TRAUMA: kinematics; hemorrhage control (tourniquet, packing, hemostatics); tension pneumo; flail chest; tamponade; evisceration; spinal precautions; TBI. BURNS: rule of nines; depth; airway burns; Parkland. SHOCK: types; stages; fluid resuscitation; classes I-IV. PEDS: PAT; Broselow; PALS; JumpSTART; abuse recognition. OB: delivery; APGAR; abnormal presentations; pre-eclampsia; neonatal resus. TOX: opioids (naloxone); organophosphate (SLUDGE); CO; decon. MCI: START; JumpSTART; ICS; NIMS. HAZMAT: placards; ERG; decon; PPE levels A-D.`;

const LOAD_MSGS=['Analyzing topic against NEMS Education Standards...','Referencing Brady, AAOS, and Jones & Bartlett textbooks...','Building course outline...','Generating slide content...','Writing instructor notes...','Aligning to NREMT scope of practice...','Finalizing curriculum package...'];
const DEL_LABELS={outline:'📋 Course outline',slides:'🖥️ Slide content',notes:'📝 Instructor notes',objectives:'🎯 Learning objectives',assessment:'✅ Assessment questions'};
const TAB_SHORT={outline:'Outline',slides:'Slides',notes:'Notes',objectives:'Objectives',assessment:'Assessment'};

let S={step:1,topic:'',detail:'',level:'EMT',duration:'2 hours',deliverables:['outline','slides','notes'],outputs:{},activeTab:''};

function render(){
  document.getElementById('app').innerHTML = stepBar() + screens[S.step]();
  bindEvents();
}

function stepBar(){
  return '<div class="stepbar">' + ['Topic','Configure','Generating','Output'].map((l,i)=>{
    const n=i+1, c='sp'+(n===S.step?' active':n<S.step?' done':'');
    return `<div class="${c}">${n<S.step?'&#10003; ':n+'. '}${l}</div>`;
  }).join('') + '</div>';
}

const screens = {
  1(){
    let opts='<option value="">&#8212; Choose a topic &#8212;</option>';
    for(const [g,list] of Object.entries(TOPICS)){
      opts+=`<optgroup label="${g}">` + list.map(t=>`<option${t===S.topic?' selected':''}>${t}</option>`).join('') + '</optgroup>';
    }
    return `<div class="card">
      <div class="ct">&#128657; Training topic</div>
      <div class="field">
        <label>Topic category</label>
        <select id="s-topic">${opts}</select>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label>Specific detail for this course</label>
        <textarea id="s-detail" placeholder="Describe the specific focus, patient population, or clinical nuance &#8212; e.g. 'Pediatric airway sizing for infants' or 'Rural EMS with 45-min transport times.'">${S.detail}</textarea>
        <div class="hint">The more detail you add, the more tailored your curriculum will be.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="btnrow"><button class="btn pri" id="bn1">Next: configure class &#8594;</button></div>`;
  },

  2(){
    const durs=['1 hour','2 hours','4 hours','8 hours','16 hours','40 hours'];
    return `<div class="card">
      <div class="ct">&#9881;&#65039; Class configuration</div>
      <div class="two">
        <div class="field">
          <label>Class duration</label>
          <select id="s-dur">${durs.map(d=>`<option${d===S.duration?' selected':''}>${d}</option>`).join('')}</select>
        </div>
        <div class="field">
          <label>Provider level</label>
          <div class="rrow">${['EMR','EMT','AEMT','Paramedic'].map(l=>`<div class="rpill${l===S.level?' sel':''}" data-lv="${l}">${l}</div>`).join('')}</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <label>Deliverables to generate</label>
        <div class="cklist">${['outline','slides','notes','objectives','assessment'].map(d=>`<label class="ckrow${S.deliverables.includes(d)?' sel':''}"><input type="checkbox" value="${d}"${S.deliverables.includes(d)?' checked':''}>${DEL_LABELS[d]}</label>`).join('')}</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="btnrow">
      <button class="btn" id="bn-back">&#8592; Back</button>
      <button class="btn pri" id="bn-gen">&#10022; Generate curriculum</button>
    </div>`;
  },

  3(){
    return `<div class="card lcard">
      <div class="spin"></div>
      <h3 id="lmsg">Building your EMS curriculum...</h3>
      <p>Referencing National EMS Education Standards &amp; current textbooks</p>
    </div>`;
  },

  4(){
    const tw = S.topic.split(' ').slice(0,3).join(' ');
    const tabs = S.deliverables.map((d,i)=>`<button class="tabbtn${i===0?' on':''}" data-tab="${d}">${TAB_SHORT[d]}</button>`).join('');
    return `<div class="mgrid">
      <div class="mt"><div class="v">${tw||'&#8212;'}</div><div class="l">Topic</div></div>
      <div class="mt r"><div class="v">${S.level}</div><div class="l">Level</div></div>
      <div class="mt o"><div class="v">${S.duration}</div><div class="l">Duration</div></div>
      <div class="mt g"><div class="v">${S.deliverables.length}</div><div class="l">Sections</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="ct">&#128218; Generated curriculum materials</div>
      <div class="tabbar">${tabs}</div>
      <div class="outbody" id="outbody">${mdRender(S.outputs[S.deliverables[0]])}</div>
    </div>
    <div class="btnrow">
      <button class="btn" id="bn-new">&#8617; New topic</button>
      <button class="btn suc" id="bn-copy">&#128203; Copy content</button>
    </div>`;
  }
};

function bindEvents(){
  const $ = id => document.getElementById(id);
  const on = (id, fn) => { const e=$(id); if(e) e.addEventListener('click', fn); };

  on('bn1', () => {
    const t = $('s-topic').value;
    if(!t){ alert('Please select a topic from the dropdown first.'); return; }
    S.topic = t;
    S.detail = $('s-detail').value.trim();
    S.step = 2;
    render();
  });

  on('bn-back', () => { S.step = 1; render(); });

  document.querySelectorAll('.rpill[data-lv]').forEach(p => {
    p.addEventListener('click', () => {
      document.querySelectorAll('.rpill[data-lv]').forEach(x => x.classList.remove('sel'));
      p.classList.add('sel');
      S.level = p.dataset.lv;
    });
  });

  document.querySelectorAll('.ckrow').forEach(row => {
    const cb = row.querySelector('input');
    row.addEventListener('click', e => {
      if(e.target !== cb) cb.checked = !cb.checked;
      if(cb.checked){
        row.classList.add('sel');
        if(!S.deliverables.includes(cb.value)) S.deliverables.push(cb.value);
      } else {
        row.classList.remove('sel');
        S.deliverables = S.deliverables.filter(x => x !== cb.value);
      }
    });
  });

  on('bn-gen', () => {
    S.duration = $('s-dur').value;
    if(!S.deliverables.length){ alert('Select at least one deliverable.'); return; }
    S.step = 3;
    render();
    generate();
  });

  document.querySelectorAll('.tabbtn[data-tab]').forEach(b => {
    b.addEventListener('click', () => {
      document.querySelectorAll('.tabbtn').forEach(x => x.classList.remove('on'));
      b.classList.add('on');
      S.activeTab = b.dataset.tab;
      $('outbody').innerHTML = mdRender(S.outputs[S.activeTab] || '');
    });
  });

  on('bn-new', () => {
    S = {step:1,topic:'',detail:'',level:'EMT',duration:'2 hours',deliverables:['outline','slides','notes'],outputs:{},activeTab:''};
    render();
  });

  on('bn-copy', () => {
    const txt = S.outputs[S.activeTab || S.deliverables[0]] || '';
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(txt).then(() => {
      const b = $('bn-copy');
      b.textContent = 'Copied!';
      setTimeout(() => { b.innerHTML = '&#128203; Copy content'; }, 2000);
    }).catch(() => alert('Select the text manually to copy.'));
  });
}

let loadTmr;
async function generate(){
  let li = 0;
  const lm = () => document.getElementById('lmsg');
  loadTmr = setInterval(() => {
    li = Math.min(li+1, LOAD_MSGS.length-1);
    if(lm()) lm().textContent = LOAD_MSGS[li];
  }, 1900);

  const dStr = S.deliverables.map(d => DEL_LABELS[d].replace(/^.+? /, '')).join(', ');
  const prompt = `You are an expert EMS curriculum developer with deep knowledge of National EMS Education Standards and EMS textbooks (Brady, AAOS, Jones & Bartlett).

TOPIC: ${S.topic}
SPECIFIC DETAIL: ${S.detail || 'Standard evidence-based content.'}
PROVIDER LEVEL: ${S.level}
CLASS DURATION: ${S.duration}
DELIVERABLES: ${dStr}

Reference: ${EMT_KB}

FORMATTING RULES:
- Start each deliverable with "## [NAME]" on its own line
- For slides: "SLIDE N: Title" then bullet points then "Speaker note: [text]"
- Be clinically accurate for ${S.level} scope of practice
- Include timing in outlines, action-verb objectives, MCQ rationales

Generate all requested deliverables now:`;

  try {
    const res = await fetch('/api/generate', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ messages: [{ role: 'user', content: prompt }] })
    });

    clearInterval(loadTmr);

    if(!res.ok){
      const err = await res.json().catch(() => ({}));
      throw new Error(err.error || `Server error ${res.status}`);
    }

    const data = await res.json();
    if(data.error) throw new Error(data.error);

    const text = data.content?.find(b => b.type === 'text')?.text || '';
    if(!text) throw new Error('Empty response from AI');

    parseOutput(text);

  } catch(err) {
    clearInterval(loadTmr);
    console.error('Generate failed:', err.message);
    showError(err.message);
    setTimeout(() => useFallback(), 800);
  }
}

function showError(msg){
  document.getElementById('app').innerHTML =
    stepBar() +
    `<div class="errbanner">&#9888;&#65039; Could not reach AI service: ${msg}. Showing a sample curriculum instead.</div>` +
    screens[3]();
}

function parseOutput(raw){
  const km = {
    outline: ['COURSE OUTLINE','OUTLINE'],
    slides:  ['SLIDE CONTENT','SLIDES','POWERPOINT'],
    notes:   ['INSTRUCTOR NOTES','INSTRUCTOR','FACILITATION'],
    objectives: ['LEARNING OBJECTIVES','OBJECTIVES'],
    assessment: ['ASSESSMENT','QUIZ','EVALUATION']
  };
  S.outputs = {};
  const chunks = raw.split(/(?=^## )/im);
  S.deliverables.forEach(d => {
    const keys = km[d] || [d.toUpperCase()];
    let found = '';
    chunks.forEach(c => {
      const h = c.split('
')[0].toUpperCase();
      if(keys.some(k => h.includes(k))) found += c;
    });
    if(!found && d === S.deliverables[0]) found = raw;
    S.outputs[d] = found;
  });
  S.activeTab = S.deliverables[0];
  S.step = 4;
  render();
}

function useFallback(){
  const t=S.topic, l=S.level, d=S.duration, det=S.detail ? '

Specific focus: '+S.detail : '';
  S.outputs.outline = `## Course outline: ${t}

Provider level: ${l} | Duration: ${d}${det}

### Learning objectives
1. Recognize signs and symptoms requiring ${l}-level intervention
2. Perform systematic patient assessment per NEMS standards
3. Apply ${l} scope-of-practice treatment protocols in priority order
4. Document and communicate patient information accurately

### Session timing
- Introduction and pre-test (10 min)
- Pathophysiology and epidemiology (20 min)
- Patient assessment: primary and secondary survey (25 min)
- ${l} treatment interventions (30 min)
- Scenario-based skill stations (40 min)
- Debrief, Q&A, and post-test (15 min)

### Key content areas
- Anatomy and pathophysiology of ${t}
- Typical and atypical presentations
- Assessment findings: history, physical exam, vital sign patterns
- ${l} scope interventions
- Transport decision-making and destination criteria`;
  S.outputs.slides = `## Slide content: ${t}

SLIDE 1: Introduction
- Why ${t} matters for ${l} providers
- Epidemiology and call frequency
- Today's learning objectives
- Pre-test baseline
Speaker note: Open with a real dispatch scenario. Ask students what they expect to find before showing answers.

SLIDE 2: Pathophysiology
- Key anatomical structures involved
- Disease or injury process
- How pathology creates the clinical picture
- Age-related considerations
Speaker note: Use anatomical models. Verify prerequisite knowledge before advancing.

SLIDE 3: Scene size-up and primary survey
- BSI/PPE and ongoing scene safety
- MOI/NOI recognition and resource needs
- AVPU and ABCDE primary survey
- Immediate life threats to correct
Speaker note: Walk through a simulated scene approach.

SLIDE 4: History and secondary assessment
- SAMPLE key questions for this condition
- OPQRST symptom characterization
- Physical exam findings
- Vital sign patterns and trends
Speaker note: Role-play history with a student as patient.

SLIDE 5: ${l} interventions
- Life threat management in priority order
- Positioning and oxygen therapy
- Medications within ${l} scope
- Reassessment after each intervention
Speaker note: Reference local protocols.

SLIDE 6: Transport and hand-off
- Load-and-go vs. stay-and-play criteria
- Destination selection
- SBAR report to receiving facility
- Documentation requirements
Speaker note: Practice SBAR verbal reports during every scenario.`;
  S.outputs.notes = `## Instructor notes: ${t}

### Pre-class preparation
- Review current local protocols
- Stage equipment at skill stations
- Prepare 2-3 patient scenarios with realistic vitals

### Core teaching points
**Treat what you find, not what dispatch tells you** — Reinforce systematic assessment before treatment.
**${l} scope clarity** — Define exactly what a ${l} can and cannot do.
**Reassessment is mandatory** — After every intervention, reassess and document response.

### Common student errors
- Skipping reassessment after interventions
- Not considering differential diagnoses
- Scene safety complacency
- Incomplete documentation

### Debrief guide
1. What did the team do well?
2. What was the highest-priority intervention?
3. What would change on the next call?
4. What questions remain?`;
  S.outputs.objectives = `## Learning objectives: ${t}

Upon completing this ${d} course, ${l} students will:

**Cognitive**
1. Describe the pathophysiology and clinical significance of ${t}
2. Identify findings indicating a time-critical emergency
3. Explain ${l} treatment priorities in correct sequence

**Affective**
4. Demonstrate professional communication with patients and families

**Psychomotor**
5. Perform a focused assessment and obtain relevant history
6. Implement ${l} interventions in correct priority order`;
  S.outputs.assessment = `## Assessment questions: ${t}

**Question 1**
After scene safety and BSI, your FIRST clinical action is:
A) Establish IV access  B) Apply oxygen at 15 L/min  C) Perform primary survey (ABCDE)  D) Contact medical control
Answer: C — Assessment always precedes treatment.

---

**Question 2**
Which finding indicates immediate transport?
